No, much about the same. You see, dad moved - he moved two or three times, quite near at hand you see. He used to get in trouble with his rents or some - thing, I don't know why - never told us why but - we lived on the Crescent. That was a ver
y nice time and then - we moved to Melrose Villas from there to the Lawn in Church Street and - from there dad took a shop on New Road Hill. But - that didn't do - very much better so we moved to another shop further along. And he had a large garden there
 and that more - he was more contented and used to - sell the fancy - fancy goods - baskets, babies cradles and all }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15532693\charrsid9731846 whickers}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
